    <h2 style="font-size: 35px; text-align: center; color: #00a7cc ">Water Parameters</h2>
    <section>
      <h3>EC</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 0.5 mS/cm</li>
        <li>Maximum: 2.0 mS/cm</li>
        <li>Note: Electrical conductivity correlates with TDS, so values within this range are generally acceptable.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>SG</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 1.000</li>
        <li>Maximum: 1.000</li>
        <li>Note: Any deviation in S.G. could indicate contamination; pure water has an S.G. of 1.000.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h3>Salinity</h3>
      <ul>
      <li>Minimum: 0 ppt</li>
      <li>Maximum: 0.5 ppt (parts per thousand)</li>
      <li>Note: Ideally, drinking water should have very low salinity. Values within this range are considered acceptable.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h3>ORP</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 200 mV</li>
        <li>Maximum: 600 mV</li>
        <li>Note: ORP within this range indicates that the water has adequate disinfection and is safe for drinking.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>TDS</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 300 mg/L (ppm)</li>
        <li>Maximum: 500 mg/L (ppm)</li>
        <li>Note: While the acceptable range is 300-500 mg/L, up to 1000 mg/L is considered the upper limit for drinkable water. However, lower values are preferable for taste and health.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>pH</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 6.5</li>
        <li>Maximum: 8.5</li>
        <li>Note: The ideal pH for drinking water is between 6.5 and 8.5 to avoid acidity or alkalinity.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Temperature</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: 10°C</li>
        <li>Maximum: 25°C</li>
        <li>Note: While temperature isn't directly harmful, water within this range is considered ideal for drinking.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
